headline: Asian markets mixed ahead of US data, expected Fed rate cut
summary: Asian markets struggled into the weekend on Friday following a bland lead from Wall Street as a mixed bag of US data did little to move the needle on expectations the Federal Reserve will cut interest rates next week.And while figures Thursday on jobless claims and layoffs came in slightly better than expected, markets have priced the chances of a rate cut Wednesday at around 90 percent.

headline: Asian markets rise ahead of US data, expected Fed rate cut
summary: Most Asian markets rose going into the weekend Friday following a broadly positive lead from Wall Street as a mixed bag of US data did little to change expectations the Federal Reserve will cut interest rates next week.After a slow start in Asia, most markets enjoyed a positive run-in to the weekend.
